/*! \mainpage Main Page
 *
 * \section intro_sec Introduction
 *
 * Textpresso is a C++ library to index scientific papers by their textual content. It exposes functions to convert
 * papers from pdf or xml formats into CAS files, and functions to store and retrieve documents from an index based on
 * Lucene search engine.
 *
 * The main classes of the library are \ref tpc::index::IndexManager, which contains methods for creating and updating
 * Textpresso index from CAS files and to search the indexed documents, and \ref tpc::cas::CASManager, to convert pdf
 * and xml files into CAS files, adding annotations about the content of the documents.
